    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey,\n\nI'm currently working full time on bringing Instantsearch to React. You can track my progress on the instantsearch-react\\* branches.\n\nIf everything goes as planned, we should have something out by the end of August.\n\nFor now, you can use the [`react-algoliasearch-helper`](https://github.com/algolia/react-algoliasearch-helper). It's largely inspired by Redux, and allows you to connect your UI components to the state of an [`algoliasearch-helper`](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js).\n",
